quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,25,""
  50,26,""
  50,27,"His companion (Satan - devil)] will say: "
  51,19,"And in their properties there was the right of the Sâ’il (the beggar who asks) and the Mahrûm (the poor who does not ask others){1}.",footnotes:1:{51:19} See the footnote of (Verse 4:37).
  51,20,"And on the earth are signs for those who have Faith with certainty."
  51,21,"And also in your ownselves. Will you not then see?"
  52,10,"And the mountains will move away with a (horrible) movement."
  52,11,"Then woe that Day to the beliers.{1}",footnotes:1:{52:11} See the footnote of {17:97}.
  52,12,"Who are playing in falsehood{1}.",footnotes:1:{52:12} Busy in disbelief and evil deeds in this world, that are trials (for mankind), and they are ignoring their eternal end (i.e. punishment in the Fire of Hell, forever).
  53,4,"It is only a Revelation revealed."
  53,5,"He has been taught (this Qur’ân) by one mighty in power [Jibrîl (Gabriel)]"
  53,6,"One free from any defect in body and mind then he (Jibrîl - Gabriel in his real shape as created by Allah) rose and became stable."